document_data.Description:
Sapphire was found in shades of pale blue to deep azure. A typical specimen had a base value of 1,000 gp.

Sapphires were considered sacred by followers of [[Aerdrie Faenya]], [[Deep Duerra]], [[Eldath]], [[Gaerdal Ironhand]]&mdash;appropriate for sacrifice, or to be consecrated for use, or recognized as boons or omens when found. Black sapphires specifically were recognized as a sign of approval from [[Bane]], and sacred to followers of [[Labelas Enoreth]], [[Laduguer]], [[Lolth]], [[Shargaas]], and [[Vhaeraun]].{{Cite web enhancement/Deity Do's and Don'ts|10, 11, 12, 13, 14, 15}}

In most stones, dazzling blue color of sapphires was achieved via exposing them to extremely high temperatures. This process was called "cooking". The color change was permanent, however it did not affect the gem's durability.
